race.comment: FORTUNE'S LUCK (1) switched barns and progressed nicely last time out to finish just 1.3L from the winner over 1200m at Leonora. Found this company much more to her liking and the 2kg claimer will position forward again. Suited and ready to win. HOOCHIE GUCCI (5) was narrowly beaten on the same day over 1400m. This is a bit easier and he will be fitter again. A senior hoop replaces the apprentice and he's a player. HEY BULL (4) is racing well and this is suitable. Drops back from the mile on the quick backup and that's a query. RUN TEDDY RUN (6) turned in a much better effort last time out to score by a head over 1200m at Landor. Tumbles in weight and won't be far away.
